{
  "stem": "5496.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I was so-- we were so hopeful that, you know, this is all a bad dream, and they're waiting for us at home.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We just didn't realize that-- right then and there, we didn't realize that, indeed, what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And if it did, we didn't want to face it, obviously.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So with that hope, we all tried to reach home, to see our families again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not too long.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A goodly few weeks, but not more than that, until one day they took us-- those of us who could go.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And obviously, I walked on my own.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise, I would have been taken to Sweden, as so many of the very ill, as you might know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were herded-- I mean, asked to come in these open trucks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they took us to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Actually, the first stop was Pilsen, I remember.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's where I got my first identity.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was a name, again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then to Prague, where we got Red Cross pass-- passports from the Red Cross, that I was a displaced person.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My name, such and such.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from there, whoever wanted to leave, where.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And by a roundabout way, and I have absolutely no recollection how, I got to Budapest, again, to one of these areas where all the people who were liberated were.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were posted names.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And of course, I was anxious to see whether any of my family would be on it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I didn't find them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I did find an aunt in Budapest who survived the war there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She was a distant aunt, not a real aunt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she was very nice to me, during these few days or perhaps a few weeks that I spent in Budapest, before I went to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
